node.text: @em.k.carter it shouldn’t make you skeptical. The bravery of one leads to the bravery of others. I hope you do more investigating into this story.

What you are about to read is both hard to write and read. But I ask you to read it all. I will try and keep it brief. 
Three weeks ago my entire staff at I Love Juice Bar tendered our resignations. The reason for this sudden change of events was because of a team meeting the new owner called. During this meeting he verbally assaulted every single one of my female employees including myself.  Very insinuative t-shirts were handed out as a new uniform and with these we were told we could use our bodies for more tips and ultimately to get him more money. He then announced that there would be a new district manager. This man he promoted, from within the company, has already been reported by customers and employees alike as a pervert, a flirt, and overall very unprofessional man. Other things were said and done as well. These are just two examples. 
I reported these men to corporate HR. And in response they did NOTHING about it. They turned a blind eye to our concerns and let these men continue to work with other, very young females that the new management has hired on in our place. 
I worked at Juice Bar Turkey Creek for almost four years. I made it my home and, not only my employees, but the customers too were my family. Four years of hard work and it was all washed away by a two hour team meeting where I witnessed this new owner violate every member of my team. 
I wish to come forward today just to say this is not ok! Corporations must stop turning a blind eye to those who have the courage to speak up. We are not liars. We are not being dramatic. We are men and women who just want the right to come into our place of work and not worry if we will be violated that day.
This is not a gender issue this a humanity issue! Things won’t change unless the corporations change. That won’t happen unless we the people bring these issues into the light.

#metoo 
#timesup
#metoojuicebar
Thank you for speaking out! I am so sad that this happened to you and your friends. Sending Love and Light and support your way...

Just to let everyone know... the new @cleanjuiceturkeycreek is right across the street and they treat everyone really well ;) 👏✨

@em.k.carter A quote from this T-shirt meeting from another employee that was there: “From the very beginning of the meeting, the new owner was making sexual remarks about our manager and the other women that worked there. He made comments about their bodies and was laughing like comments like that were fine.” Three employees have now come out with stories of sexual harassment. These things anger God and they should make his people angry. Also, you seem to have missed the woman next to the text wearing underwear.

@tylerdw89 it just makes me skeptical when people only come out about sexual harassment after one person posts. And yeah, sexual harassment should make God’s people angry. God’s people also strive to be like Jesus, which in my opinion is grace and forgiveness. Oh, and I hope she would be wearing underwear! It would be pornographic if she wasn’t.
@em.k.carter it shouldn’t make you skeptical. The bravery of one leads to the bravery of others. I hope you do more investigating into this story.

Just being the devil’s advocate here...I find it a little interesting that you have scripture highlighted in this post. What about scripture that talks about giving each other grace? When I first saw the T-shirt I was very confused on how it was offensive. To me, the orange and “squeeze me” was a play on words and then the figure symbolized “health” or something. I didn’t take it offensively. I’ve been into juice bar a couple of times and from what I remember they wear aprons or something (probably for sanitation reasons?) so I don’t see how this could be a uniform. I just feel like maybe the owner could use some grace just like we have all needed grace. I know I have said some horrible things to people (in the workplace and outside) in the past and boy am I glad that it didn’t make a viral post on Instagram and eventually on local TV stations.
What’s wrong with rape honestly if they’re just objects??????????????
